title: Fork, 1985-103-278-g, ca. 1700
description: Fork has three flat tines, slightly curved, waisted neck. Flat, rectangular handle, slightly tapered. Engraved on both sides with animal faces, musical instruments, scrolls and shield a shield. Inscription on the sides, floral decoration at the top.
creditline: The Robert L. Metzenberg Collection, gift of Eleanor L. Metzenberg
inscribed: On sides of handle: C. SALVIATI. OPUS. POST. COENAM. AMBULA. On small rectangular shield on back of handle: SC
markings: On handles: "ET" French import mark, 1864-1893. Tardy, SILVER, 1981. p.207
